	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=92605><span id= >Agrio</span></a><br><span id=notbold>55 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.26]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Changing Extended Affliction to Burning Affliction is an improvement in my opinion. <br><br>Extended Affl increased the duration of your dots by 20%.&nbsp;&nbsp;Nice for snare, fear, root, etc. but a limited benefit on most other dots since the biggest problem with most dots is that the fight is over before the dot does its full damage.  And even on those short duration dots (less than a minute), it doesn't give you a 20% improvement.  For example, a 7 tick dot extended 20% is 8.4 ticks.  The game does not give you that last 0.4 ticks.  So you only get 1 more tick which is less than a 20% improvement.  <br><br>Burning affliction increases the damage per tick by 20% so that even if its a short fight, you always do 20% more damage than you would have without the focus item.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
